article.headline: Cal St.-Fullerton 105, CS Northridge 86
article.story: NORTHRIDGE, Calif. -- D.J. Seeley scored a career-high 37 points to lead hot-shooting Cal State Fullerton to a 105-86 victory against Cal State Northridge on Saturday night. Kwame Vaughn added 22 points and Sammy Yeager 21 for the Titans (7-6, 1-1 Big West), who shot 58.6 percent (34 of 58) from the floor, including 12 of 23 (52.2 percent) from 3-point range. Cal State Fullerton eclipsed 100 points for the third time this season. Stephen Maxwell had 22 points and 12 rebounds and Stephan Hicks added 20 points for the Matadors (9-5, 0-2). Seeley shot 10 of 17 from the floor and made four 3-pointers. His point total tied for the fifth-highest in school history.
